                    </div>
                    <span>When I picked up Cat's Cradle, it had been a while since I had last read a Vonnegut (Slaughterhouse Five) so it was as if I was a new reader.  Cat's Cradle is like no other book I have read.  Very wry, very well crafted.  I was totally absorbed in Jonah and his journey and, of course, the fate of ice nine.  An excellent reflection on our society, while still an entertaining read.  Go on and read it already.</span>
                  
